%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Starter%20homes%20cost%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20in%20a%20record%20237%20cities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22starter%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3a2a71a227600e631e358%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FM.%20Spencer%20Green%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETypical%20starter%20homes%20are%20worth%20at%20least%20%241%20million%20in%20a%20record%20237%20US%20cities%2C%20Zillow%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStarter-home%20prices%20have%20appreciated%20faster%20than%20the%20average%20property%2C%20the%20firm%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%20half%20of%20these%20cities%20are%20in%20California%2C%20with%20New%20York%20and%20New%20Jersey%20also%20heavily%20represented.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20record%20number%20of%20US%20cities%20now%20have%20typical%20starter%20homes%20worth%20at%20least%20%241%20million%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fresearch%2Fmillion-dollar-start-home-34251%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZillow%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20homebuyers%20can%20find%20seven-figure%20starter%20properties%20in%20237%20metros%2C%20the%20firm%20said%2C%20a%20considerable%20jump%20from%20where%20values%20stood%20five%20years%20ago.%20According%20to%20the%20real-estate%20agency%2C%20only%2085%20cities%20had%20such%20high%20prices%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20defined%20typical%20starter%20homes%20as%20properties%20in%20the%20lower%20third%20of%20values.%20Given%20that%20they're%20generally%20on%20the%20more%20affordable%20side%20of%20the%20market%2C%20these%20serve%20as%20an%20entryway%20for%20first-time%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%2C%20their%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-starter-home-price-housing-affordability-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharp%20appreciation%3C%2Fa%3E%20likely%20puts%20them%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20many%20potential%20consumers%2C%20reflecting%20a%20broader%20pain%20buyers%20are%20facing%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurging%20demand%20and%20limited%20home%20supply%20have%20amplified%20housing%20unaffordability%20in%20recent%20years.%20High%20interest%20rates%20have%20only%20added%20to%20the%20scarcity%20problem%2C%20as%20these%20elevated%20borrowing%20rates%20discouraged%20many%20owners%20from%20selling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20have%20also%20had%20to%20face%20off%20against%20property%20investors%2C%20who%20snapped%20up%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-investor-purchases-affordable-homes-fourth-quarter-redfin-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20share%20of%20low-priced%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023's%20final%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20reported%20that%20starter%20home%20prices%20surged%2054.1%25%20in%20the%20five-year%20timeframe%2C%20outpacing%20the%2049.1%25%20appreciation%20of%20typical%20US%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20the%20typical%20starter%20home%20is%20worth%20%24196%2C611%20nationally%2C%20which%20Zillow%20considers%20an%20affordable%20price%20tag%20for%20the%20median-income%20buyers.%20But%2C%20%241%20million%20starter%20homes%20can%20be%20found%20in%20nearly%20half%20of%20all%20states%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20leads%20this%20trend%2C%20holding%20117%20of%20these%20metros.%20New%20York%20followed%20at%2031%2C%20ahead%20of%20New%20Jersey%20at%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20line-up%20is%20identical%20to%20a%20Zillow%20report%20from%20April%2C%20which%20tracked%20the%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-home-prices-values-zillow-outlook-mortgage-rates-inventory-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20US%20homes%20worth%20%241%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20with%20starter%20properties%2C%20a%20record%20amount%20of%20cities%20saw%20average%20home%20prices%20reach%20these%20highs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20costs%20and%20elevated%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20recently%20dented%20buyer%20appetite%2C%20which%20Zillow%20notes%20could%20bring%20about%20a%20more%20balanced%20market.%20In%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-market-prices-listings-buyers-market-inventory-texas-florida-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprices%20were%20slashed%20on%20nearly%20a%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20listed%20homes%2C%20as%20existing%20home%20sales%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-logjam-existing-home-sales-record-prices-mortgages-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efell%20to%20nearly%20their%20slowest%20pace%20since%202010%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-prices-starter-home-million-dollar-cities-home-costs-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722000413000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3a2871a227600e631e352%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-prices-starter-home-million-dollar-cities-home-costs-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20cities%20than%20ever%20have%20typical%20starter%20homes%20worth%20at%20least%20%241%20million%2C%20Zillow%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22fdemott%40insider.com%20(Filip%20De%20Mott)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-prices-starter-home-million-dollar-cities-home-costs-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22You've%20heard%20of%20pretty%20privilege%2C%20but%20'ugly%20privilege'%20may%20have%20its%20perks%20too%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225558%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20holding%20a%20plant%20in%20front%20of%20her%20face%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a21e855a8a7bf049195b27%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223705%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bugly%26quot%3B%20may%20simply%20be%20left%20alone%20to%20get%20on%20with%20their%20jobs.%3Cp%3EFreshSplash%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20TikToker%20discussed%20%26quot%3Bugly%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20she%20felt%20being%20unattractive%20to%20men%20was%20an%20advantage.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20suggest%20that%20less%20attractive%20individuals%20may%20face%20fewer%20distractions%20and%20biases%20at%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20sexism%20underlies%20any%20appearance-based%20privilege%2C%20as%20women%20are%20more%20often%20scrutinized%20for%20their%20looks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20have%20heard%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-pretty-privilege-can-affect-your-job-interview-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bpretty%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20concept%20that%20attractive%20people%20are%20considered%20to%20have%20other%20positive%20qualities%2C%20such%20as%20being%20smart%2C%20successful%2C%20and%20kind%2C%20simply%20because%20of%20their%20physical%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGood-looking%20people%20also%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeautiful-people-make-more-money-2014-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearn%20more%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20are%20put%20forward%20more%20often%20for%20promotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20about%20%26quot%3Bugly%20privilege%26quot%3B%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20TikToker%20called%20Sarah%20posted%20a%20video%20this%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sarahs.tok%2Fvideo%2F7394974990082460933%3F_r%3D1%26_t%3D8oIGOaYT4Hx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20has%20amassed%20159%2C000%20views%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20where%20she%20explained%20why%20she%20thought%20she%20had%20%26quot%3Bugly%20privilege%26quot%3B%20and%20what%20it%20meant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20when%20she%20uses%20this%20term%2C%20people%20will%20often%20correct%20her%20and%20tell%20her%20she's%20pretty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20when%20I%20say%20I%20have%20ugly%20privilege%2C%20it's%20not%20that%20I%20necessarily%20think%20I'm%20an%20ugly%20individual%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20what%20I%20mean.%20Because%20I've%20been%20told%20plenty%20of%20times%20throughout%20my%20life%20that%20I'm%20pretty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20I%20say%20I%20have%20ugly%20privilege%2C%20what%20I%20mean%20by%20that%20is%20men%2C%20in%20general%2C%20don't%20mind%20me%20attractive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20said%20that%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20men%20find%20her%20ugly%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20they%20leave%20me%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20to%20me%2C%20that's%20a%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20privilege%20to%20be%20left%20alone%20by%20men%20because%20they%20find%20me%20ugly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2262b9cb82-9162-47ad-b885-0c338a196e58%5C%22%3EA%20workplace%20advantage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlexa%20S.%20Chilcutt%2C%20an%20executive%20education%20professor%20and%20executive%20coach%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Carey%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20this%20theory%20may%20apply%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20who%20are%20'off%20the%20radar'%20physically%20may%20not%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20ancillary%20distractions%20of%20others%20vying%20for%20attention%20and%20can%20focus%20on%20and%20are%20seen%20for%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20relationships%20and%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20less%20feminine%20or%20'pretty'%20may%20work%20to%20a%20woman's%20advantage%20when%20seeking%20higher%20levels%20of%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELucas%20Botzen%2C%20an%20HR%20professional%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20workforce%20platform%20Rivermate%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20individuals%20who%20aren't%20conventionally%20attractive%20may%20be%20seen%20as%20more%20serious%20or%20diligent%20and%20%26quot%3Bmight%20enjoy%20certain%20advantages%20that%20will%20bring%20them%20professional%20freedom%20and%20less%20scrutiny%20over%20their%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployees%20who%20do%20not%20fit%20traditional%20beauty%20standards%20are%20sometimes%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20affected%20by%20certain%20biases%2C%26quot%3B%20Botzen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0749597814000715%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2014%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20professors%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado's%20business%20school%20argued%20that%20women%20deemed%20physically%20attractive%20were%20discriminated%20against%20when%20applying%20for%20jobs%20that%20were%20perceived%20as%20masculine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBotzen%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20may%20well%20have%20less%20interruption%20from%20others%20and%20less%20inappropriate%20behavior%2C%20which%20might%20enable%20them%20to%20pay%20more%20focus%20on%20their%20jobs%20and%20thus%20contribute%20accordingly%20toward%20their%20role.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBotzen%20said%20attractive%20people%20who%20receive%20attention%20for%20their%20looks%20may%20also%20be%20under%20pressure%20to%20maintain%20that%20standard.%20Not%20feeling%20that%20pressure%20could%20be%20professionally%20advantageous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20time%20and%20energy%20can%20be%20forwarded%20to%20their%20job%20rather%20than%20being%20wasted%20on%20others'%20expectations%20about%20the%20way%20a%20person%20should%20look%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20this%20concentration%20can%20result%20in%20better%20performance%20and%20greater%20productivity.%20This%2C%20again%20purely%20on%20merit%2C%20can%20bring%20in%20promotions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e224b69a-e2ce-43cf-8ce3-780da9435bd6%5C%22%3EUnderlying%20sexism%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bprivilege%26quot%3B%20of%20being%20deemed%20ugly%20or%20pretty%2C%20women%20are%20disproportionately%20scrutinized%20for%20their%20looks%20and%20are%20acutely%20aware%20of%20this%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehrdirector.com%2Fwomen-bosses-still-judged-looks-smarts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201%2C000%20female%20and%201%2C000%20male%20employees%2C%2092%25%20of%20women%20respondents%20aged%2024%20to%2035%20said%20that%20professional%20women%20were%20judged%20more%20for%20their%20appearance%20than%20professional%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESinclair%20Pharma%20surveyed%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsinclairprodstorage.blob.core.windows.net%2Fmedia%2Fpodjqnsy%2Fexternal_maili-survey-report-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%2C000%20women%20globally%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%2097%25%20believed%20women%20face%20judgment%20for%20their%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppearance%20plays%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20how%20women%20are%20perceived%20and%20treated%20in%20the%20workplace%20than%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20woman%20called%20Melissa%20Weaver%20told%20a%20story%20on%20TikTok%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-seeking-vp-job-hr-told-her-appearance-not-good-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eof%20a%20recent%20interview%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20job%20she%20was%20perfect%20for.%20Despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquestions-to-ask-in-job-interview-to-get-the-role-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egiving%20a%20killer%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20checking%20all%20the%20boxes%20for%20the%20role%2C%20she%20was%20rejected.%20The%20hiring%20manager%20told%20her%20she%20hadn't%20put%20enough%20%26quot%3Beffort%26quot%3B%20into%20her%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20Weaver%20could%20think%20of%20to%20justify%20this%20comment%20was%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-not-hired-for-wearing-no-makeup-too-common-experts-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe%20didn't%20wear%20makeup%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniela%20Herrera%2C%20a%20talent%20and%20recruitment%20expert%20and%20founding%20partner%20of%20Allies%20in%20Recruiting%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20employers%20%26quot%3Bstill%20uphold%20very%20outdated%20and%20inequitable%20stereotypes%20and%20biases%20at%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20hiring%20managers%20reject%20candidates%20based%20on%20the%20clothes%20they%20wear%20to%20an%20interview%2C%20the%20color%20of%20the%20candidate's%20hair%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftattoos-shouldnt-be-important-in-job-interviews-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20tattoos%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20their%20physical%20attributes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20also%20still%20subjected%20to%20sexist%20comments.%20Chilcutt%20said%20a%20male%20attorney%20once%20told%20her%20it%20was%20a%20good%20thing%20she%20didn't%20have%20%26quot%3Blarge%20breasts%26quot%3B%20because%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Balready%20attractive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20did%2C%20no%20one%20would%20see%20that%20you're%20intelligent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20remembers%20him%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBotzen%20said%20people%20who%20aren't%20conventionally%20attractive%20don't%20automatically%20win.%20He%20suggested%20people%20considered%20unattractive%20c