%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereported%20in%201924%20that%20the%20property%20had%20been%20built%20for%20Olympians%20and%20had%20living%20quarters%2C%20a%20dining%20hall%2C%20and%20a%20recreation%20center.%20The%20estate%20also%20had%20stables%20for%20the%20team's%20polo%20horses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20officials%20slept%20comfortably%20inside%20the%20estate's%20mansion%20and%20female%20athletes%20occupied%20gatehouses%20on%20the%20property%2C%20the%20male%20athletes%20slept%20in%20modest%20barracks%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20when%20we%20arrived%20that%20they%20had%20built%20some%20prefab%20houses%20made%20of%20pressed%20board%2C%20and%20they%20were%20pretty%20austere%2C%26quot%3B%20William%20Neufeld%2C%20a%20US%20javelin%20thrower%2C%20recalled%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigital.la84.org%2Fdigital%2Fcollection%2Fp17103coll11%2Fid%2F228%2Frec%2F49%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20LA84%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E's%20oral%20history%20series%20published%20in%201987.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20army%20cots%20with%20thin%20mattresses%2C%20and%20they%20had%20canvas%20sheets%20for%20us%2C%20which%20were%20pretty%20rough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20chair%20or%20two%2C%20and%20that%20was%20our%20furniture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeufeld%20said%20that%20because%20the%20field%20at%20the%20estate%20was%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20rough%2C%26quot%3B%20athletes%20had%20to%20travel%20by%20%26quot%3Blumbering%20buses%26quot%3B%20to%20train%20at%20Colombes%20Stadium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecollections%20suggest%20that%20the%20female%20athletes'%20accommodations%20at%20the%20gatehouses%20were%20better.%20Aileen%20Riggin%2C%20a%20medal-winning%20diver%20and%20swimmer%2C%20remembered%20%26quot%3Bwinding%20paths%20and%20rose%20gardens%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20heavenly%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22