20Neruda%20of%20Urdu%20poetry.%20But%20it%20would%20be%20as%20precise%20to%20call%20him%20the%20John%20Donne%20of%20'Indian%20popular%20culture'.%20And%20I%20use%20this%20composite%20phrase%20instead%20of%20'Hindi%20cinema'%20or%20'Bollywood'%20because%20a%20bulk%20of%20Gulzar%20saab's%20unexplored%20philosophical%20insights%20far%20exceed%20his%20filmography%2C%20poetry%2C%20and%20writings.%20What%20is%20often%20missed%20in%20his%20language%20and%20poetics%20are%20his%20metaphors%20from%20quantum%20mechanics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20'Phenomenological'%20Poet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201934%20in%20Deena%2C%20now%20in%20the%20Jhelum%20district%20of%20present-day%20Pakistan%2C%20Gulzar%20saab's%20early%20life%20and%20his%20harrowing%20journey%20to%20India%20before%20the%20Partition%20of%201947%20-%20memories%20that%20found%20lauded%20expressions%20in%20Shyam%20Benegal's%201994%20classic%2C%20%3Cem%3EMammo%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E-%20would%20make%20for%20a%20fertile%20backdrop%20for%20many%20a%20biographer.%20But%20not%20many%20may%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20cosmic%20and%20quantum-like%20figures%20of%20speech%20that%20decorate%20his%20perceptions%20of%20reality.%20%26quot%3BNASA%20is%20my%20favourite%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20Gulzar%20once%20acknowledged.%20%26quot%3BThe%20universe%20with%20its%20abstract%20nature%20attracts%20me.%20The%20abstract%20element%20in%20my%20poetry%20comes%20from%20there.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fwhy-the-left-is-weak-today-in-india-according-to-gulzar-488966%5C%22%3EWatch%C2%A0%7C%C2%A0Why%20Th%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fwhy-the-left-is-weak-today-in-india-according-to-gulzar-488966%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ee%20Left%20Is%20Weak%20Today%20In%20India%2C%20According%20To%20Gulzar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20Gulzar%20saab's%20modesty%20allowed%20him%2C%20instead%20of%20calling%20his%20poetry%20%26quot%3Babstract%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20might%20have%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bphenomenological%26quot%3B.%20The%20word%20'phenomenology'%20means%20the%20study%20of%20experience%2C%20along%20with%20studying%20the%20nuances%20'qualia'%2C%20that%20is%2C%20the%20way%20fundamental%20units%20of%20reality%20are%20experienced.%20Gulzar%20saab's%20poetry%20often%20represents%20reality%20in%20minuscule%20slices.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EQatra%20qatra%20milti%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bdroplets%20and%20droplets%20appear%20to%20us%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EIjaazat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201987)%2C%20or%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ejale%20qatra%20qatra%2C%20gale%20qatra%20qatra%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bthe%20kindling%20of%20slivers%2C%20the%20melting%20of%20slivers%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3ESaathiya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%202002).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20certain%20other%20cases-as%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Emain%20chaand%20nigal%20gayi%2C%20daiyya%20re%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BI%20swallowed%20the%20moon%2C%20my%20gosh!%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EOmkara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%202006)-Gulzar%20saab%20appears%20to%20swap%20the%20microscopic%20reality%20for%20the%20cosmic%2C%20where%20swallowing%20the%20moon%20signifies%20the%20quest%20of%20a%20mythical%20oscillatory%20body%2C%20or%2C%20in%20worldly%20terms%2C%20a%20lover%20in%20heat%20who%20swallowed%20the%20moon%20to%20soothe%20herself.%20%C2%A0However%2C%20his%20deeper%20aesthetic%20sense%20resurfaces%20in%20moon-related%20metaphors%20elsewhere%2C%20as%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Edhaage%20tod%20laao%20chandni%20se%20noor%20ke%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bpluck%20slivers%20of%20moonlight%20from%20the%20cosmic%20ray%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EJhoom%20Barabar%20Jhoom%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%202007).%20The%20metaphor%20reminds%20one%20of%20that%20famous%20'double%20slit'%20science%20experiment%2C%20where%20photons%20split%20to%20reveal%20wave-particle%20duality.%20Gulzar%20saab's%20words%20are%20nowhere%20'abstract'.%20In%20a%20liminal%20way%2C%20they%20escort%20the%20listener%20into%20a%20scientific%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReality%2C%20Bite-Sized%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20miniaturisation%20of%20reality%20or%20spacetime%20has%20over%20the%20last%20century%20come%20to%20be%20known%20to%20physicists%20as%20'quantisation'.%20Neither%20poets%20nor%20quantum%20mechanics%20have%20a%20monopoly%20over%20the%20art%20of%20quantising.%20However%2C%20both%20enchant%20us%20by%20deconstructing%20and%20experiencing%20reality%20at%20a%20subatomic%20level.%20Among%20physicists%20and%20mathematicians%20who%20did%20that%20with%20ease%20and%20panache%2C%20we%20recall%20James%20Maxwell%2C%20Werner%20Heisenberg%2C%20Erwin%20Schr%C3%B6dinger%2C%20Wolfgang%20Pauli%2C%20Paul%20Dirac%2C%20David%20Bohm%2C%20and%20even%20modern-day%20names%20like%20Sean%20Carroll%20and%20Jim%20Al-Khalili.%20Among%20psychologists%20and%20cultural%20thinkers%2C%20we%20find%20Carl%20Jung%20and%20Jiddu%20Krishnamurti%20at%20the%20helm.%20And%2C%20among%20poets%2C%20Gulzaar%20saab%20qualifies%20as%20a%20natural%20citizen%20of%20a%20sphere%20that%20was%20once%20dominated%20by%20Albert%20Einstein's%20contemporaries%2C%20W.B.%20Yeats%2C%20T.S.%20Eliot%2C%20and%20Ezra%20Pound%20(to%20take%20a%20reference%20from%20Daniel%20Albright's%201997%20study%2C%20%3Cem%3EQuantum%20Poetics%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fgulzar-on-why-he-doesnt-intend-to-return-to-films-1978649%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0Gulzar%20On%20Why%20He%20Doesn't%20Intend%20To%20Return%20To%20Films%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20amusing%20and%20staggering%20at%20once%20to%20witness%20how%20quantum%20entities-whether%20with%20conscious%20will%20or%20subconscious%20genius-inform%20Gulzar%20saab's%20figures%20of%20speech.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EIk%20baar%20waqt%20se%20lamha%20gira%20kahin%2F%20wahan%20daastan%20mili%2C%20lamha%20kahin%20nahin%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bonce%20upon%20a%20fickle%20time%2C%20a%20moment%20dropped%20somewhere%2F%20there%20a%20legend%20sprouted%20its%20wings%2C%20and%20blurred%20the%20moment%20in%20air%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EGol%20Maal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201979).%20Heisenberg's%20uncertainty%20principle-that%20is%2C%20the%20limits%20of%20human%20measurements%20in%20calculating%20the%20momentum%20and%20position%20of%20subatomic%20particles%20simultaneously-is%20writ%20large%20upon%20this%20couplet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERevelling%20In%20Uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20scheme%20of%20uncertainty%20becomes%20both%20ambivalent%20and%20yet%20emboldened%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Eyaar%20misaal-e-os%20chale%2C%20paayon%20ke%20tale%20firdaus%20chale%2F%20kabhi%20daal%20daal%2C%20kabhi%20paat%20paat%2C%20main%20hawa%20pe%20dhundun%20uske%20nishaan%2F%20sar-e-ishq%20ki%20chaaon%20chal%2F%20chhaiyan%20chhaiyan%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bmy%20beloved%20trails%20a%20dewy%20guise%2C%20as%20her%20toes%20sail%20aloft%20paradise%2F%20from%20branch%20to%20branch%2C%20from%20leaf%20to%20leaf%2C%20I%20search%20the%20wind%20for%20her%20trace%2Fwalk%20in%20the%20shade%20of%20heavenly%20love%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EDil%20Se%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201998).%20Undoubtedly%2C%20these%20words%20are%20addressed%20to%20a%20cosmic%20being%20personified%20as%20the%20beloved.%20The%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20beloved's%20shapeshifting%20forms%20reminds%20one%20of%20Biblical%2C%20Quranic%20and%20Upanishadic%20figures%20of%20speech.%20But%20in%20these%20words%20is%20again%20embedded%20that%20poetical%20quantisation%3A%20the%20ransacking%20of%20woods%20and%20the%20wind%20to%20spot%20and%20accord%20a%20location%20to%20a%20formless%20beloved.%20If%20this%20were%20science%20itself%2C%20it%20would%20almost%20be%20akin%20to%20the%20despair%20of%20the%20observers%20of%20the%20double-slit%20experiment%2C%20struggling%20to%20measure%20quantum%20entities%20in%20waves%2C%20particles%2C%20or%20definable%20units%20of%20spacetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fgulzar-on-his-scribblings-i-am-not-an-artist-763006%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0Gulzar%20on%20His%20'Scribblings'%3A%20I%20am%20Not%20an%20Artist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20these%20two%20couplets%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ehumne%20dekhi%20hai%20un%20aankhon%20ki%20mahakti%20khushbu%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20the%20wafting%20fragrance%20of%20those%20eyes%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EKhamoshi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201969)%2C%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Eapki%20aankhon%20me%20kuchh%2C%20mahke%20huye%20se%20raaz%20hain%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Byour%20eyes%20are%20the%20home%20of%20fragrant%20mysteries%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EGhar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201978).%20There%20are%20critics%20who%20could%20never%20understand%20how%20%26quot%3Beyes%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bvision%26quot%3B%20could%20be%20compared%20to%20the%20senses%20of%20smell%20and%20odour.%20Yet%2C%20these%20lines%20contain%20scintillating%20lessons%20for%20those%20studying%20the%20philosophy%20of%20quantum%20mechanics.%20As%20Al-Khalili%20explains%20in%20his%20documentary%20%3Cem%3ESecrets%20of%20Quantum%20Physics%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2015)%2C%20the%20human%20perception%20of%20smell%20is%20processed%20through%20a%20%26quot%3Bquantum%20nose%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20interprets%20molecular%20oscillations%20as%20particles%2C%20not%20waves.%20Essentially%2C%20our%20%26quot%3Bquantum%20nose%26quot%3B%20is%20capable%20of%20evoking%20certain%20memories%20through%20certain%20odours%2C%20which%20are%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20produced%20by%20molecular%20configurations%20that%20are%20of%20a%20highly%20visual%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELove%2C%20Longing%2C%20And%20Everything%20Else%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20critics%20who%20fail%20to%20sense%20Gulzar%20saab's%20brilliance%20are%2C%20in%20Eliot's%20words%2C%20like%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ordinary%26quot%3B%20being%20whose%20%26quot%3Bexperience%20is%20chaotic%2C%20irregular%2C%20fragmentary%26quot%3B%2C%20to%20whom%20reading%20great%20philosophy%20and%20falling%20in%20love%20%26quot%3Bhave%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20each%20other%2C%20or%20with%20the%20noise%20of%20the%20typewriter%20or%20the%20smell%20of%20cooking%26quot%3B%3B%20nevertheless%2C%20in%20%26quot%3Bthe%20mind%20of%20the%20poet%20these%20experiences%20are%20always%20forming%20new%20wholes%26quot%3B.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20Indian%20poet%2C%20the%20legendary%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%2C%20took%20science%20very%2C%20very%20seriously.%20He%20had%20once%20met%20Einstein%20to%20discuss%20a%20scheme%20of%20galactic%20union%20between%20science%20and%20poetry%3B%20the%20West%20and%20the%20East%3B%20the%20human%20and%20the%20divine%3B%20the%20quantum%20and%20the%20cosmic.%20One%20such%20union%20also%20appears%20in%20Gulzar%20saab's%20famous%20ghazal%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Eruke%20ruke%20se%20qadam%2C%20ruk%20ke%20baar%20baar%20chalen%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bthese%20hesitant%20feet%20have%20again%20hesitated%2C%20and%20they%20have%20walked%20again%26quot%3B%3B%20%3Cem%3EMausam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201975%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EMammo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%201994).%20There%20is%20an%20unmistakable%20Upanishadic%20allegory%20in%20the%20lines%20that%20follow%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Euthaaye%20phirte%20hain%20ehsaan%20jism%20ka%20jaan%20par%2F%20chalen%20jahaan%20se%20to%20ye%20pairahan%20utaar%20ke%20chalen%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BI%20have%20carried%20the%20burden%20of%20my%20flesh%20on%20my%20being%2F%20when%20I%20leave%20the%20world%2C%20I'll%20take%20off%20this%20garb%26quot%3B).%20In%20%3Cem%3EMausam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20this%20divide%20between%20the%20garb%20and%20the%20soul%20symbolises%20a%20permanent%20truth%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20separation%20of%20lovers.%20In%20%3Cem%3EMammo%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20symbolises%20the%20enduring%20pangs%20of%20the%20Partition.%20Like%20logic%20and%20love%2C%20like%20waves%20and%20particles%2C%20the%20lines%20distinguish%20between%20the%20'garb'%2C%20the%20material%20aspect%2C%20and%20'soul'%2C%20the%20immaterial%20aspect%20of%20human%20life.%20One%20cannot%20exist%20without%20the%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmall%20Things%20In%20A%20Big%20World%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20non-duality%20is%20brought%20to%20life%20magnificently%20in%20these%20lines%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Eaadmi%20bulbula%20hai%20paani%20ka%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bhumanity%20is%20a%20bubble%20in%20water%26quot%3B)%20...%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ena%20samundar%20nigal%20saka%20usko%2F%20na%20tvareekh%20tod%20paayi%20hai%2F%20waqt%20ki%20hatheli%20par%20behta%2F%20aadmi%20bulbula%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bneither%20the%20ocean%20has%20engulfed%20it%2F%20nor%20has%20history%20deconstructed%20it%2F%20like%20lines%20that%20crisscross%20the%20palm%20of%20time%2F%20humanity%20is%20a%20bubble%20in%20water%26quot%3B).%20Gulzaar%20saab%20refrains%20from%20ascribing%20primacy%20to%20the%20ocean%2C%20the%20origin%20of%20life%2C%20or%20to%20human%20life%20itself.%20Instead%2C%20Gulzar%2C%20the%20poet%20of%20cosmic%20and%20quantum%20consciousness%2C%20is%20like%20the%20microscopists%20of%20philosopher%20G.K.%20Chesterton%2C%20who%20%26quot%3Bstudy%20small%20things%20and%20live%20in%20a%20large%20world%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFeeling%20bedazzled%2C%20bemused%2C%20belittled%20before%20Gulzar's%20poetical%20expressions%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20us%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20our%20infinitesimal%20place%20in%20the%20universe%2C%20and%20understanding%20it%20in%20infinite%20metaphysical%20feelings.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20thankful%20to%20Harshita%20Mishra%20and%20Nitin%20Thakur%20for%20their%20valuable%20insights.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Arup%20K.%20Chatterjee%20is%20Professor%20of%20English%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721994540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2F1623rh1o_gulzar_625x300_26_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpresenting-gulzar-a-poet-of-love-and-quantum-mechanics-6192704%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bulk%20of%20Gulzar%20saab's%20unexplored%20philosophical%20insights%20far%20exceed%20his%20filmography%2C%20poetry%2C%20and%20writings.%20What%20is%20often%20missed%20in%20his%20language%20and%20poetics%20are%20his%20metaphors%20from%20quantum%20mechanics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpresenting-gulzar-a-poet-of-love-and-quantum-mechanics-6192704%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpresenting-gulzar-a-poet-of-love-and-quantum-mechanics-6192704%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpresenting-gulzar-a-poet-of-love-and-quantum-mechanics-6192704%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paris%20Olympics%20Opening%20Ceremony%3A%20Performers%2C%20Timing%20And%20All%20Other%20Details%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Opening%20Ceremony%20of%20Paris%20Olympics%202024%20is%20set%20to%20be%20the%20one%20of%20its%20kind%20with%20the%20event%20set%20to%20take%20place%20at%20the%20Seine%20River%20in%20the%20French%20capital.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20ever%2C%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20will%20be%20held%20outside%20a%20stadium%2C%20instead%20the%20city%20of%20Paris%20will%20be%20turned%20into%20a%20grand%20arena.%20A%20whopping%2010%2C500%20athletes%20are%20set%20to%20sail%20across%20the%20Seine%2C%20and%20the%20two%20representatives%20for%20India%20are%20veteran%20table%20tennis%20star%20Achanta%20Sharath%20Kamal%20and%20shuttler%20PV%20Sindhu.%20The%20Opening%20Ceremony%20is%20expected%20to%20start%20at%2011%20PM%20IST%20(7%3A30%20PM%20local%20time).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BFirst%20of%20its%20kind%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20Opening%20Ceremony%20is%20concerned%2C%20it%20won't%20take%20place%20inside%20a%20stadium%20this%20time.%20The%20Seine%20River%20in%20Paris%20will%20witness%20almost%20100%20boats%20carrying%20an%20estimated%2010%2C500%20athletes%20will%20float%20along%20the%20Seine%20during%20the%20parade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajority%20of%20the%20206%20National%20Olympic%20Committees%20(NOCs)%20represented%20in%20the%20parade%20will%20have%20boats%20to%20themselves%2C%20while%20the%20smaller%20ones%20will%20share%20boats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20boats%20will%20be%20equipped%20with%20cameras%20to%20allow%20television%20and%20online%20viewers%20to%20see%20the%20athletes%20up%20close.%20The%20boat%20parade%20will%20conclude%20after%20covering%20a%206-kilometre%20route%20at%20the%20Trocadero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Olympics'%20official%20website%2C%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20is%20open%20to%20as%20many%20people%20as%20possible%20is%20a%20first.%20Eighty%20giant%20screens%20and%20strategically%20placed%20speakers%20will%20allow%20everyone%20to%20enjoy%20the%20magical%20atmosphere%20of%20this%20show%20reverberating%20throughout%20the%20French%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Opening%20Ceremony%20for%20the%20Olympic%20Games%20Paris%202024%20will%20be%20the%20largest%20in%20Games%20history.%20It%20will%20be%20open%20to%20all%3A%20residents%20from%20Paris%20and%20its%20region%2C%20as%20well%20as%20visitors%20from%20all%20over%20France%20and%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EParade%20route%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20parade%20will%20commence%20at%20the%20Austerlitz%20bridge%20(East)%20beside%20the%20Jardin%20des%20Plantes%20and%20will%20conclude%20at%20the%20Trocadero%20(West).%20The%20opening%20ceremony%20make%20its%20way%20around%20the%20two%20islands%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20city%20(the%20Ile%20Saint%20Louis%20and%20the%20Ile%20de%20la%20Cite)%20before%20passing%20under%20several%20bridges%20and%20gateways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAthletes%20on%20board%20the%20parade%20boats%20will%20get%20glimpses%20of%20some%20of%20the%20official%20Games%20venues%2C%20including%20Parc%20Urbain%20La%20Concorde%2C%20the%20Esplanade%20des%20Invalides%2C%20the%20Grand%20Palais%2C%20and%20lastly%20the%20Iena%20bridge%20where%20the%20parade%20will%20come%20to%20a%20stop%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerformers%20and%20star%20attractions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20multiple%20reports%2C%20singers%20Celine%20Dion%20and%20Lady%20Gaga%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20perform.%20French-Malian%20R%26amp%3BB%20star%20Aya%20Nakamura%20is%20also%20rumoured%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20star-studded%20line-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721994480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2F8d9j08r_paris-olympics-2024_625x300_25_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fparis-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-performers-timing-venue-and-all-other-details-6186247%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20the%20first%20time%20ever%2C%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20will%20be%20held%20outside%20a%20stadium%2C%20instead%20the%20city%20of%20Paris%20will%20be%20turned%20into%20a%20grand%20arena.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fparis-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-performers-timing-venue-and-all-other-details-6186247%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fparis-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-performers-timing-venue-and-all-other-details-6186247%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fparis-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-perfor