BYou%20can%20think%20of%20Musk's%20contribution%20as%20an%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Gerhardt%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20administrative%20law%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BTo%20eliminate%20any%20governmental%20interference%20with%20his%20businesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20owns%20six%20companies%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20subject%20to%20regulations%20from%20different%20agencies%20controlled%20by%20the%20executive%20branch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conservative-controlled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-strips-sec-enforcement-power-financial-fraud-jarkesy-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court's%20recent%20SEC%20v.%20Jarkesy%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20along%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-chevron-doctrine-bidens-climate-policies-at-risk-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELoper%20Bright%20decision%20striking%20down%20much%20of%20the%20Chevron%20doctrine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20federal%20agencies%20to%20enforce%20laws%20and%20regulations%20against%20companies.%20But%20with%20Trump%20as%20president%2C%20Musk%20wouldn't%20even%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-decisions-chevron-sec-federal-government-regulations-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edismantle%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3Badministrative%20state%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20federal%20agencies%20out%20of%20his%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20head%20of%20the%20executive%20branch%2C%20the%20president%20can%20simply%20sign%20executive%20orders%20and%20make%20hiring%20decisions%20to%20change%20the%20direction%20of%20federal%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%2C%20SpaceX%2C%20and%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20are%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.madisontrust.com%2Finformation-center%2Fvisualizations%2Feverything-elon