%20protect%20environments%20due%20to%20construction%2C%20according%20to%20Jilian%20Blanchard%2C%20an%20environmental%20lawyer%20at%20Lawyers%20for%20Good%20Government.%20But%20a%20president%20could%20make%20it%20even%20easier%20for%20companies%20to%20challenge%20regulations%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFederal%20environmental%20rules%20like%20NEPA%20require%20you%20to%20do%20all%20sorts%20of%20environmental%20analysis%20before%20you%20build%20out%20a%20big%20manufacturing%20plant%2C%20for%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%3ENational%20Environmental%20Policy%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20a%20federal%20rule%2C%20so%20it%20comes%20across%20the%20whole%20country%20no%20matter%20where%20he%20decides%20to%20move%20his%20plants%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExisting%20federal%20laws%20from%20the%20EPA%20and%20Department%20of%20Interior%20could%20be%20relaxed%2C%20Blanchard%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Trump%20were%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20he%20would%20control%20the%20EPA%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20EPA%2C%20and%20they%20could%20also%20amend%20those%20regulations%20to%20make%20the%20permitting%20for%20Clean%20Water%20Act%20requirements%20easier%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSame%20is%20true%20for%20the%20Endangered%20Species%20Act%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20agencies%20%E2%80%94%20called%20independent%20agencies%20%E2%80%94%20have%20statutory%20independence%20from%20the%20executive%20branch.%20The%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20which%20has%20overseen%20numerous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-sec-probe-reason-to-support-trump-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigations%20into%20Musk%20and%20his%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20years%2C%20is%20one%20of%20them.