%80%99s%20taste.%20Usually%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20take%20hot%20curry%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20cook%20it%20with%20yoghurt%20and%20cream.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWho%20is%20taking%20the%20prize%20home%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20really%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20debate%2C%20was%20a%20speech%20made%20in%202001%20by%20the%20then-British%20foreign%20secretary%20Robin%20Cook%20who%20hailed%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctrue%20British%20national%20dish%E2%80%9D.%20Indians%20weren%E2%80%99t%20thrilled%20with%20this%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Cook%20went%20on%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6not%20only%20because%20it%20is%20the%20most%20popular%2C%20but%20because%20it%20is%20a%20perfect%20illustration%20of%20the%20way%20Britain%20absorbs%20and%20adapts%20external%20influences.%20Chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F60553%2Fhistory-biryani-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20Indian%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3Esauce%20was%20added%20to%20satisfy%20the%20desire%20of%20British%20people%20to%20have%20their%20meat%20served%20in%20gravy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20attempt%20in%202009%20to%20pin%20the%20dish%E2%80%99s%20origin%20to%20Europe%20when%20Mohammad%20Sarwar%2C%20then%20Labour%20MP%20for%20Glasgow%20Central%2C%20campaigned%20for%20the%20dish%20to%20be%20given%20EU%20Protected%20Designation%20of%20Origin%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20motion%20was%20tabled%20by%20the%20House%20of%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FTzYACT9nT7A%3Fsi%3Dl7zeE0Cp3SioKMoC%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20starting%20to%20think%20that%20the%20war%20of%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20origins%20were%20just%20between%20the%20two%20subcontinents%20(India%20and%20Europe)%2C%20you%20are%20wrong.%20Even%20within%20India%2C%20the%20origin%20stands%20to%20be%20debated%20%E2%80%94%20is%20it%20Mogul%20or%20%3Cem%3EPunjabi%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZaeemuddin%20Ahmad%20of%20the%20iconic%20Karim%E2%80%99s%20restaurant%20in%20Delhi%2C%20is%20of%20the%20first%20opinion%2C%20saying%20the%20recipe%20was%20passed%20down%20through%20the%20generations%20in%20his%20family.%20As%20he%20relayed%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Daily%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CChicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20authentic%20Mughlai%20recipe%20prepared%20by%20our%20forefathers%20who%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F157345%2Fmughal-emperor-mughlai-food-history-india-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroyal%20chefs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Mughal%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20food%20critic%20Rahul%20Verma%20claims%20to%20have%20first%20tasted%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201971%20and%20insists%20it%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3EPunjabi%20%3C%2Fem%3Edish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20belief%20is%20shared%20by%20many%20who%20see%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20a%20mutation%20of%20the%20butter%20chicken%2C%20which%20is%20(and%20this%20is%20set%20in%20stone)%20the%20creation%20of%20Kundan%20Lal%20Gujral%2C%20the%20man%20behind%20Moti%20Mahal%20restaurant%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20look-alikes%2C%20the%20butter%20chicken%20and%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20differ%20in%20their%20taste%20palate%20and%20the%20hero%20ingredient%20(aside%20from%20chicken)%20that%20they%20feature%3B%20the%20former%20has%20copious%20amounts%20of%20butter%2C%20and%20a%20sweeter%20taste%2C%20while%20the%20latter%20is%20on%20the%20spicier%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaved%20Nasir%2C%20executive%20chef%20of%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20popular%20Dishoom%20does%20not%20favour%20this%20opinion%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebeing%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20butter%20chicken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20526px)%20100vw%2C%20526px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22526%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20chicken%20tikka%20masala%20is%20said%20to%20be%20an%20invention%20by%20Bangladeshi%20chef%20and%20Shish%20Mahal%20chef%20Ali%20Ahmed%20Aslam%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543.jpg%20526w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543-500x500.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2F227376692_2808545786123429_4439602653112633831_n-1721035543-96x96.jpg%2096w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356878%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22526%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20chicken%3Cem%3E%20tikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20said%20to%20be%20an%20invention%20by%20%3Cem%3EBangladeshi%20%3C%2Fem%3Echef%20and%20Shish%20Mahal%20chef%20Ali%20Ahmed%20Aslam%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Facebook%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FCoriandersIndian%2Fposts%2Fchicken-tikka-masala-its-a-classic-for-a-reason-delicious-flavourful-not-too-hot%2F2808546092790065%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoriander%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20didn%E2%80%99t%20originate%20from%20India%2C%20first%20of%20all.%20There%20is%20a%20history%20of%20butter%20chicken%2C%20which%20comes%20from%20a%20place%20called%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F316761%2Fhistory-and-origin-of-tandoor-from-indus-valley-to-moti-mahal-kundal-lal-gujral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMoti%20Mahal%20in%20Old%20Delhi%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%5BIt%20came%5D%20over%20here%20as%20the%20recipe%20of%20the%20butter%20chicken.%20I%20think%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%20%3C%2Fem%3Eactually%20happened%20here%20in%20the%20UK.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20people%20know%20that%20this%20was%20the%20dish%20that%20was%20invented%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20culinary%20experts%20aren%E2%80%99t%20backing%20down%20from%20whose%20brainchild%20the%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereally%20was%2C%20it%20seems%20foodies%20around%20the%20world%20aren%E2%80%99t%20too%20bothered%20by%20this.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20table%20has%20a%20good%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%20As%20a%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%20dating%20back%20to%202007%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20organisers%20of%20the%20National%20Curry%20Week%20have%20estimated%20that%20if%20all%20the%20portions%20of%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20consumed%20annually%20in%20the%20country%20were%20stacked%20on%20top%20of%20one%20another%2C%20they%20would%20form%20a%20tower%202%2C770%20times%20taller%20than%20the%20Greenwich%20Millenium%20Dome.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20chance%20that%20the%20present%20statistics%20have%20outranked%20these.%20Questions%20about%20the%20ethnicity%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Emight%20always%20remain%20unanswered.%20But%20we%20can%20all%20agree%20on%20one%20thing%3B%20whoever%20came%20up%20with%20this%20ingenious%2C%20humble%2C%20versatile%20dish%20has%20a%20special%20place%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhomegrown.co.in%2Fhomegrown-explore%2Fthe-controversial-history-of-chicken-tikka-masala%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Controversial%20History%20Of%20Chicken%20Tikka%20Masala%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Homegrown%2C%20Published%20on%208%20June%202021.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.littleindiaofdenver.com%2Fblog%2Fchicken-tikka-masala-unravelling-the-history-behind-it%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChicken%20Tikka%20Masala%3A%20Unravelling%20The%20History%20Behind%20It%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Little%20India%20of%20Denver%2C%20Published%20on%2030%20December%202022.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.willflyforfood.net%2Funited-kingdom-what-is-the-true-origin-of-chicken-tikka-masala-recipe%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20the%20True%20Origin%20of%20Chicken%20Tikka%20Masala%3F%20(Recipe)%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Will%20Fly%20for%20Food%2C%20Published%20on%2016%20January%202024.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%2